---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <main class="prose mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-24">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: June 2026</p>
    <p>CampSoon provides a browser extension that helps users monitor supported campsite reservation systems and receive availability alerts. This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how to contact us.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account information:</strong> email address, authentication status, and basic account records needed to provide the service.</li>
      <li><strong>Monitor settings:</strong> campsite search preferences, trip dates, supported park provider selections, alert settings, and related configuration that you create in the extension.</li>
      <li><strong>Points and billing records:</strong> point balances, package purchases, payment status, refunds, and transaction history related to CampSoon point packages.</li>
      <li><strong>Support information:</strong> messages, receipts, account details, and diagnostic information you choose to send when requesting help.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical information:</strong> logs and device or browser information needed to operate, secure, troubleshoot, and improve the service.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Payments</h2>
    <p>CampSoon point package purchases are processed through Stripe Checkout. We do not store full card numbers for CampSoon purchases on our servers. Stripe may process payment details, billing details, fraud prevention signals, and checkout metadata according to Stripe's own terms and privacy practices. CampSoon receives limited payment status and transaction information needed to credit points, provide receipts, support refunds, and resolve billing issues.</p>

    <h2>Browser Extension and Local Data</h2>
    <p>The CampSoon extension stores some settings locally in your browser so the extension can operate on your device. We do not ask for or store official park reservation account passwords on CampSoon servers. Information that remains local to your browser is controlled through your browser and extension settings.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide campsite monitoring, account access, alerts, point balances, and billing support.</li>
      <li>To process point package purchases, refunds, and payment-related customer support.</li>
      <li>To secure the service, prevent abuse, diagnose technical issues, and maintain service reliability.</li>
      <li>To respond to support, legal, compliance, and safety requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Sharing</h2>
    <p>We share information only with service providers needed to run CampSoon, such as payment processing, hosting, email delivery, analytics, security, and support tools, or when required by law. We do not sell personal information.</p>

    <h2>Retention and Deletion</h2>
    <p>We keep account, monitor, billing, and support records for as long as needed to provide the service, meet legal and accounting obligations, prevent abuse, and resolve disputes. You can request account deletion or data access by contacting support@campsoon.com.</p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational safeguards to protect CampSoon account and billing records. No online service can guarantee absolute security.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy requests, data access, deletion, or security questions, contact <strong>support@campsoon.com</strong>.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
